cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the analysis of logic programs, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on the combination of set-sharing with freeness and linearity information, which involves abstract interpretation and abstract domains, making it relevant to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the implementation of the abstract unification operator, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
